THE National Museum of Tanzania (NMT) has announced a comprehensive plan to build a state of the art Presidential Museum in Dodoma in the next financial year. Minister of Tourism and Natural Resources, Damas Ndumbaro made the announcement on Friday when tabling the Ministry’s budget estimates and expenditures to the Parliamentarians in Dodoma. Dr Ndumbaro stated that the NMT aims at preserving the country’s heritage and promoting tourism through museum. “The plan is to build and renovate some existing structures used to collect and preserve the country’s heritage,” he said. The plan is to ensure the museums contribute potentially as another tourism market. It was not identified how much has been allocated for the project but the minister insisted the project must be implemented during the 2021/22 Financial Year. 